      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-03T04:51:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done, but this feels very rats-nesty:\n\n  // Make sure that the basic load command structure doesn’t overflow the\n  // space allotted for load commands, as well as iterating through ncmds.\n  uint32_t cmd_size \u003d 0;\n  for (uint32_t cmd_index \u003d 0;\n       cmd_index \u003c header-\u003encmds \u0026\u0026 cmd_size \u003c header-\u003esizeofcmds;\n       cmd_index++, cmd_size +\u003d command-\u003ecmdsize) {\n\n\nWith this at the end of the loop:\n    const uint8_t* header_ptr \u003d\n        reinterpret_cast\u003cconst uint8_t*\u003e(command) + command-\u003ecmdsize;\n    command \u003d reinterpret_cast\u003cconst load_command*\u003e(header_ptr);\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "9a830a5f_9925935a",
      "revId": "fbc3fd552020e02915cb8485c64d3ebe42bb2bd3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
