      "message": "If we’re going to be using this code from our final signal handler, logging is out.\n\nBut we won’t want to adhere to the snapshot interface for anything in our final signal handler. There’s no reason to adhere to that interface, and it hampers flexibility in making the purpose-built thing that we need fit the purpose as closely as possible (meaning doing it with as few unsafe things as possible).\n\n(For example, some things in the snapshot interface return vectors, and vectors allocate memory…)",
